Head (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF5FFC4FEF4F8363C64F851" box="[272,352,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 1.04–1.11 times as long as wide; punctation very dense, moderately coarse, distinctly umbilicate, interstices lacking microsculpture; postocular portion approximately 1.7–2.0 times as long as eye length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF4FFC5FF23FF133E6CFF64" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF4FFC5FEA1FF133C93FF2C" box="[325,407,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 1.07–1.17 times as long as wide, 0.94–0.98 times as long and 0.88–0.97 times as broad as head; punctation non-umbilicate, moderately dense and as coarse as that of head; midline posteriorly with short and narrow impunctate elevation; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF4FFC5FF23FE873885FEDC" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF4FFC5FEFAFE873C76FE80" box="[286,370,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 0.66–0.74 times as long as wide, 0.56–0.59 times as long and 0.91–0.95 times as broad as pronotum; punctation as dense as, and slightly coarser than that of pronotum; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF4FFC5FF23FECF3932FE14" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Abdomen with punctation dense and rather coarse on tergites III–V, dense and less coarse on tergite VI, moderately dense and fine on tergites VII–VIII; interstices lacking microsculpture.</paragraph>
<caption id="579B57D2FFF4FFC5FF73F9383E3BF965" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" startId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" targetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF4FFC5FF73F9383E3BF965" blockId="5.[151,1436,1724,1784]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FF73F9383C50F949" bold="true" box="[151,340,1724,1748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">FIGURES 18–22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C4E47CD9FFF4FFC5FEBFF9393F2AF949" authorityName="Lin, Yu &amp; Hu" authorityYear="2022" box="[347,558,1724,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leigongensis">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FEBFF9393F2AF949" box="[347,558,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Nazeris leigongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FDD0F9383F49F949" bold="true" box="[564,589,1724,1748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">18</emphasis>
forebody; 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FD59F9383FD2F949" bold="true" box="[701,726,1724,1748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">19</emphasis>
male sternite VII; 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FC73F9383EB4F949" bold="true" box="[919,944,1724,1748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">20</emphasis>
male sternite VIII; 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FB9DF9383996F949" bold="true" box="[1145,1170,1724,1748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">21</emphasis>
aedeagus in ventral view; 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FF73F9643DB4F965" bold="true" box="[151,176,1760,1784]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">22</emphasis>
aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FDCFF9643F40F965" bold="true" box="[555,580,1760,1784]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">18</emphasis>
1.0 mm; 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FD41F9643FE1F965" bold="true" box="[677,741,1760,1784]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">19–22</emphasis>
0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF4FFC5FF23F8A239B1F830" blockId="5.[151,1437,1830,2037]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Male. Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF4FFC5FE55F8A23F03F8DC" box="[433,519,1830,1857]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin nearly truncate at middle. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF4FFC5FAE4F8A23852F8DC" box="[1280,1366,1830,1857]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) with triangular posterior excision. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF4FFC5FD85F8CE3FE7F8F8" box="[609,739,1866,1893]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Figs 21, 22</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized; ventral process wide and short, with nearly truncate or slightly concaved apex in ventral view; dorso-lateral apophyses moderately strong, with wide and round apex in ventral view, nearly straight in lateral view, extending beyond apex of ventral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF4FFC6FF23F83239EFFE81" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF4FFC5FF23F8323E3CF868" blockId="5.[151,1437,1830,2037]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF4FFC5FF23F8323F36F84C" bold="true" box="[199,562,1974,2001]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Distribution and habitat data.</emphasis>
The species is known from Leigong Mt. in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="C120C9B8FFF4FFC5FB60F83239ECF84D" box="[1156,1256,1974,2000]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were collected by sifting leaf litter at an altitude of 
<quantity id="C41CAABFFFF4FFC5FD31F85E3E30F868" box="[725,820,2010,2037]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="m" value="1550.0">1,550 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF7FFC6FF23FF1239EFFE81" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF7FFC6FF23FF123CB5FF2D" bold="true" box="[199,433,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is similar in general appearance and tergites characters to 
<taxonomicName id="C4E47CD9FFF7FFC6FAE2FF133DF3FF49" authority="Hu &amp; Li" authorityName="Hu &amp; Li" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congchaoi">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF7FFC6FAE2FF133899FF2D" box="[1286,1437,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">N. congchaoi</emphasis>
Hu &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="67757AABFFF7FFC6FEE2FF3E3CD0FF49" author="Hu, J. Y. &amp; Li, L. Z." box="[262,468,186,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref5761" refString="Hu, J. Y. &amp; Li, L. Z. (2015) The Nazeris Fauna of the Luoxiao Mountain Range, China. (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae). Plos One, 10 (7), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0131942" type="journal article" year="2015">Hu &amp; Li 2015: 11</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF7FFC6FE04FF3E3F20FF48" box="[480,548,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,533,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-159@2.[151,1436,525,1910]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Habitus 1 N. ingentis; 2 N. resimus; 3 N. leigongensis; 4 N. yujiei; 5 N. muricatus; 6 N. excertus; 7 N. serratus. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), but can be separated by the wider posterior excision of male sternite VIII, by the much shorter ventral process (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF7FFC6FDF6FF5A3F60FF65" box="[530,612,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) and much wider dorso-lateral apophyses of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF7FFC6FB37FF5A3822FF65" box="[1235,1318,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF7FFC6FF23FE863C4AFE81" bold="true" box="[199,334,258,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet derived from Leigong Mt., where the species was discovered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
